          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A cocktail of secondary beams was produced via the",
                "fragmentation of an intense 95 MeV/nucleon 32-S-16+",
                "primary beam on a thick carbon target.Fourteen ion",
                "species 13B, 14C, 15,16N, 16,17O, 18,19F, 19,20Ne,",
                "21Na, 22Mg, 23Al and 24Si with energies between 24",
                "and 60 MeV/nucleon and intensities ranging from 30",
                "and 7000 pps were obtained. We had about 300 pps of",
                "23Al at 57 MeV/nucleon."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.By knowing the value of the primary beam",
                "intensity, the intensities of the secondary beams were",
                "derived from several empty-target normalization runs.",
                "The final cross sections were determined using an",
                "average of these normalization runs, estimated that the",
                "normalization uncertainty is 11%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainties contain only statistical and",
                "calculation contributions, but not the overall 11%",
                "uncertainty in the cross section normalization."
              ]
            },
